n over rivers, O Supreme Mother ruling over all, you, having left the heart=
 of the supreme Lord, grow and expand.
 
Brief Purport: Water evaporating f=
rom the ocean forms clouds. Clouds give rains and that forms rivers. If wat=
er does not evaporate from the ocean, all water will be in the ocean and th=
ere will be oneness. But because of the separation, there are multiple bodi=
es of water. But rivers do try to unite with the ocean (original source) at=
 some stage or the other.
 
